PBB <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BivinSadler/MSDS_6306_Doing-Data-Science/Master/Unit%202/PlayersBBall.csv")
#Q1 Summarize the number of players in each position
PBB %>% ggplot(aes(x=position)) + geom_bar() + theme_update(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + ggtitle("Number of Players in Each Position") + xlab("Position Played") 

#Q2 Investigate if the distribution of the weight of centers is > weight of forwards
PBB %>% ggplot(aes(x=position, y=weight,color=position)) + geom_bar(stat="identity") + theme_update(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + ggtitle("Distribution of Weights") + xlab("Position Played") + ylab("Weight (lbs)")
## Warning: Removed 6 rows containing missing values (position_stack).

#Q3/Q4 Investigate if the distribution of the weight of centers is > height of forwards
PBB %>% ggplot(aes(x=position, y=height,color=position)) + geom_bar(stat="identity") + theme_update(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + ggtitle("Distribution of Heights") + xlab("Position Played") + ylab("Height (ft)")

#Q5/Q6 Investigate players height related to weight
ggplot(data=PBB,mapping=aes(x=height,y=weight,linetype=position, color=position)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth() + theme_update(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + ggtitle("Distribution of Height vs Weight") + xlab("Height (ft)") + ylab("Weight (lbs)")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 6 rows containing non-finite values (stat_smooth).
## Warning: Removed 6 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

#Q7 Height over the years
ggplot(data=PBB, mapping=aes(x=year_start, y=height)) + geom_boxplot() + theme_update(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + ggtitle("Distribution of Player Heights over Time") + xlab("Player Start Year") + ylab("Height (ft)")

#Q8 3D plot of height vs weight vs years
p <- plot_ly(PBB,x=~height,y=~weight,z=~year_start,color=~position) %>% 
               add_markers() %>% 
               layout(scene=list(xaxis=list(title='Height'),
                                 yaxis=list(title='Weight'),
                                 zaxis=list(title='Player Start Year')))
